President Trump held his first Cabinet meeting with General Kelly as Chief of Staff. Trump praised Kelly's previous work at Homeland Security, specifically in stopping illegal immigration. Trump also highlighted the positive state of the economy, mentioning the highest stock market in history, a GDP growth of 2.6%, and the lowest unemployment rate in 17 years. He expressed confidence that General Kelly will be an excellent Chief of Staff and stated that his administration will work hard to make America great again. When asked about North Korea, Trump assured that they will handle the situation. The meeting ended at 10:10 A.M. EDT.